\begin_layout Subsection
PaperRank-Hirsch index
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is a proposed alternative to h-index which uses the calculated PaperRanks.
 The PaperRanks are normalized to represent more meaningful quantities,
 namely the most probable number of citations which the node might receive,
 the 
\begin_inset Formula $Q$
\end_inset

-value.
 The index is then defined as the integer number 
\begin_inset Formula $h$
\end_inset

 such that an author has at least 
\begin_inset Formula $h$
\end_inset

 papers with 
\begin_inset Formula $Q$
\end_inset

-value greater than or equal to 
\begin_inset Formula $h$
\end_inset

.
